    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_byjyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>byjyn</orth><form type="variant"
                            >(<orth>bijyn</orth>)</form><form type="participle"
                        ><orth>byd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bijun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>bid</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вить</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>whirl</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>плести (например, косу)</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>braid</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>скручивать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>twist</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ʒykkūtæ byjyn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">заплетать косы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">braid one's hair</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>byd byjyn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">плести тесьму</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">make lace</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kaw byjyn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">плести плетень</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">wattle</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>rūvas bændæn byjyn bajdydta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лиса стала вить веревку</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the fox began to %bmake%b the rope</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dywwæ styr kawy sbydtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сплели два больших плетня</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>two big wattles were wattled</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>bæxi dumæg ka bidta?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто заплетал хвост лошади?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>who braided the horse’s tail?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            155</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>oj færstæ æsqærcægæj bid iskind æj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>его (дóма) стены сплетены из кольчуги</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>its (of the house) walls are %bmade of%b chain mail</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Корень *%ivi%i-; общеиндоевропейское слово: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ptw’y-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                            /><biblScope>570</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                                    /><biblScope>570</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vayati</w>
                        <gloss><q>он плетет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">вити</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>вить</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>výti</w>
                        <gloss><q>скручивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>viēre</w>
                        <gloss><q>плести</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Переход <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>v</w></mentioned> → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>b</w></mentioned> в начальном положении необычен (закономерно
                    %iv%i→%iw%i), но все же есть помимо %ibyjyn%i еще несколько надежных случаев:
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> (←<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>vāra-</w></mentioned>) ‘воля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bællyn"/> (←
                        <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>varya-</w></mentioned>) ‘хотеть’. — Прош, причастие %ibyd%i | %ibid%i (=
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vīta</w></mentioned>) лексикализовалось в значении ‘тесьма’.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 85, III
                            157</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>33</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The root *%ivi%i-; a common Indo-European word: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ptw’y-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                            /><biblScope>570</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"
                                    /><biblScope>570</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vayati</w>
                        <gloss><q>he braids</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>viti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>vitʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>výti</w>
                        <gloss><q>twist</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>viēre</w>
                        <gloss><q>braid</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The transition of the
                        <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>v</w></mentioned> → <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>b</w></mentioned> is unusual in the initial position (the regular one is
                    %iv%i→%iw%i), but there are still few reliable cases apart from %ibyjyn%i: <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> (←<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>vāra-</w></mentioned>) ‘will’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bællyn"/> (←
                        <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>varya-</w></mentioned>) ‘want’. — The past participle %ibyd%i | %ibid%i
                    (= <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vīta</w></mentioned>) is lexicalized in the meaning
                            'darkness'.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>II 85, III 157</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>33</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
